The paper deals with the problem of verifying the null space condition in compressed sensing, which is a fundamental problem in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithms involve optimization techniques and machine learning methods, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic of interest in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of subsets and cardinality in the problem formulation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new sandwiching algorithm, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI).
